   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>The <fr:link href="/jms-00KI/" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KI/" display-uri="jms-00KI" type="local">identity function</fr:link> is clearly <fr:link href="/jms-00KI/" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KI/" display-uri="jms-00KI" type="local">injective</fr:link>, as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0=a_1]]></fr:tex> implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0=a_1]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\rightarrowtail  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\rightarrowtail  C]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="/jms-00M0/" title="The axiom of infinity" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M0/" display-uri="jms-00M0" type="local">injections</fr:link>. To show that the <fr:link href="/jms-00KI/" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KI/" display-uri="jms-00KI" type="local">composite function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f\colon  A\to  C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injective</fr:link>, we fix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0,a_1\in  A]]></fr:tex> to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a_0\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} = g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0=a_1]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injective</fr:link>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a_0\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>; therefore, because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injective</fr:link>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0=a_1]]></fr:tex> as desired.</html:p>
